history.content:
I took 162 fall junior year, a year after 61C. About the team thing, being great is good, I'd say most important is team synergy. You want teammates you can rely on at 2am. 

Conceptually, I think 162 is very rich. It's impressive to be able to talk about all the low-level systems things during interviews, and know exactly what's going on. You should try to make significant contributions to the projects to get good takeaways from the class. You'll also get better at coding C.

The tests and the projects seem a little misaligned. The projects are heavy coding based, and one small error is super costly in time to find and fix. So although you get a really firm understanding of the project and its related stuff, the tests touch on other things too. Like general OS/systems trivia seeming, with some fair coding parts. Don't skip discussion, go to a great TA's section and learn the fuck out of the stuff. It's interesting and tough and makes you all the more tougher after you take it.

Good luck!

children.subject: I'm in the course this semester and have a great group, so projects have gone well and have not been too stressful. I've personally found the homeworks not too bad. The exams are the hard part of this class for me. Students I talked to in the past didn't stress exams being an difficult part of the class, but don't discount them. Projects aren't the only thing that matters in this class!
